OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FSwansea: Hairdryer safety  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Falert after house fire     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An overheated hairdryer left on a pile 
OL,6, of clothing is believed to have caused 
OL,7, a house fire, prompting a safety alert.
OL,9,FThree fire crews tackled the bedroom   
OL,10,Fblaze at a property at Ravenhill,      
OL,11,FSwansea, on Thursday.                  
OL,13,FWill Bowen, from Mid and West Wales    
OL,14,FFire and Rescue Service, said          
OL,15,Fhairdryers could pose a risk as they   
OL,16,F"stay hot for some time" after use.    
OL,18,F"You should place it on a non-flammable
OL,19,Fsurface and away from any other        
OL,20,Fcombustible items," he said.           
